- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the stability and continuity of different centrality measures, which involves algorithmic and computational aspects. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve software implementation and testing of the proposed centrality measures. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also possible as the paper deals with network analysis, but it is less likely as the focus is on graph theory rather than network protocols or architectures. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the least likely category as the paper does not involve any machine learning techniques or models.
